ions turns out to be very important in this\ncase in order to apply the correct $\\gamma$-ray strength function in the\nHauser-Feshbach calculations. The model also reproduces cross-section values of\n$\\alpha$-induced reactions on $^{106}$Cd, as well as of ($\\alpha$,n) reactions\non $^{115,116}$Sn, hinting at a more global character of the obtained\nnuclear-physics input.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Mar 2015 12:32:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-18"}
