d\n(0.74$\\pm$0.48) x 10$^{-3}$ to (0.88$\\pm$0.56) x 10$^{-3}$ objects per cubic\nparsec in the T1-T4.5 range. There seem to be an excess of objects in the L/T\ntransition with respect to the late T dwarfs, a discrepancy that could be\nexplained assuming a higher binary fraction than expected for the L/T\ntransition, or that objects in the high-mass end and low-mass end of this\nregime form in different environments, i.e. following different IMFs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Mar 2015 14:58:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-24"}
